Patch Set 3: Workflow-1

Well it was more or less a straight copy and paste from what eventlet was doing. (which I assume I'm gonna have to modify it a lot before we can land this, because it clearly doesn't work: http://logs.openstack.org/51/492651/4/check/gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-full-ubuntu-xenial/1e4fde8/logs/screen-g-api.txt.gz?level=TRACE#_Aug_14_21_26_10_831716 ) The bit here that is tricky is that we we don't have any control on the data length from uwsgi. We call chunked_read() and it gives us the chunk, regardless of the length parameter on the read() call. So we need to loop to match the chunksize with the requested read length. I'm also pretty sure I screwed up the length arithmetic because the eventlet read call on the chunked data has a length parameter and uwsgi.chunked_read() doesn't.

The other thing this is likely missing is other file like properties and functions on the UWSGIChunkFile class. I assumed if there were any other requirements it would shake loose from testing. But none of the jobs have gotten far enough yet.

This is very much a WIP still, I was just using the gate to do testing, and gerrit to save state.

Patch Set 4:

This makes a lot of sense. The main thing I can think of that it would be important to confirm is that the read method is indeed being called with length values most of the time (presumably by logging it).

If not, then this is generating the same memory problem as other efforts.

Once there's info on the value of the length inputs we can make some discoveries on whether it is ever smaller than the length of the data from chunked_read and if so, if that matters (I wouldn't think so in a python context).

Really nice work teasing this out.
